            <div type="section" xml:id="Legislation">
                <head>Legislation</head>
                <p> Access to Estonian Archives is legislated by the Public Information Act that
                    gives the public the right to request access to government documents. However,
                    state secrets are not covered by the Act. </p>
            </div>
            <div type="section" xml:id="Location">
                <head>Location</head>
                <p> Archives of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Estonia, Islandi v√§ljak
                    1, Tallinn.</p>
                <p> State Archives, 24 Madara Street, Tallinn. </p>
            </div>
            <div type="section" xml:id="Procedures">
                <head> Procedures</head>
                <p> Researchers should first contact the State Archives to request in writing access
                    to the relevant documents. </p>
            </div>
